We were motivated by a belief that the MBTA's Green Line stops too frequently.
This interactive map shows optimal stops based on different calculated 
<i>k</i>-means scores for clustering the Green Line T stops in Boston. The 
variant of the clustering algorithm takes into account a given weight for each 
point, and the weight is a function of the stop's current popularity and the 
proximity to the nearest alternative stop (measured by walking distance).

Initally, the map shows the current existing Green Line stops (where <i>k</i> = 
0). Call those <i>x</i>. By playing with the sliders and changing the 
value of <i>k</i>, you can see the optimal <i>k</i> stops for that branch, 
suggesting all other <i>x - k</i> are the ones to eliminate if aiming for that
level of scaling back.

var colors = {'GLB':'red', 'GLC':'green', 'GLD':'brown', 'GLE':'blue'};
var branches = ['GLB','GLC','GLD','GLE'];

// draw a point for all stops
branches.forEach(function(branch) {
  // find the id for all stops on this line
  stops = t_branch_info.filter(function(stop) {
    return stop.line == branch;
  });
  // now get the coordinates for that stop id to draw it
  stops.forEach(function(stop) {
    loc = t_stop_locations.filter(function(l) {
      return l.stop_id == stop.stop_id;
    });
    L.circle([loc[0].stop_lat, loc[0].stop_lon], 30, {
      color: colors[branch],
      fillColor: 'white',
      fillOpacity: 0.9
    }).addTo(map).bindPopup(stop.pretty_name);
  });
});

// Track the markers added for means so they can be removed.
var meanMarkers = {'GLB':[], 'GLC':[], 'GLD':[], 'GLE':[]};

function drawkmeans(k, branch) {
  // Find the id for all stops on this line.
  means = optimal_green_stops.filter(function(stop) {
    return stop.line == branch &&
           stop.k == k;  
  });
  // Delete what means existed already for this branch.
  if(meanMarkers[branch]) {
    meanMarkers[branch].forEach( function(marker){ map.removeLayer(marker); } );
  }
  meanMarkers[branch] = []
  // Now draw new ones.
  means.forEach(function(mean) {
    mean.coords.forEach(function(crds) {
      var marker = new L.circleMarker([crds.stop_lat, crds.stop_lon], {
        radius: 5,
        stroke: true,
        color: 'black',
        fillColor: colors[branch],
        fillOpacity: 0.9
      });
      marker.addTo(map).bindPopup('Optimal Stop');
      // Save it
      meanMarkers[branch].push(marker);
    });
  });
}

// Then draw/interact with the k-means.
var k = 9
drawkmeans(9)

$("#bslider").slider({
  range: "max",
  value: 0,
  min: 0,
  max: 23,
  slide: function(event, ui) {
    drawkmeans(ui.value, 'GLB');
    $( "#bsliderval" ).text(ui.value);
  }
});
drawkmeans(0, 'GLB'); // init
$( "#bsliderval" ).text(0);

$("#cslider").slider({
  range: "max",
  value: 0,
  min: 0,
  max: 21,
  slide: function(event, ui) {
    drawkmeans(ui.value, 'GLC');
    $( "#csliderval" ).text(ui.value);
  }
});
drawkmeans(0, 'GLC'); // init
$( "#csliderval" ).text(0);

$("#dslider").slider({
  range: "max",
  value: 0,
  min: 0,
  max: 18,
  slide: function(event, ui) {
    drawkmeans(ui.value, 'GLD');
    $( "#dsliderval" ).text(ui.value);
  }
});
drawkmeans(0, 'GLD'); // init
$( "#dsliderval" ).text(0);

$("#eslider").slider({
  range: "max",
  value: 0,
  min: 0,
  max: 19,
  slide: function(event, ui) {
    drawkmeans(ui.value, 'GLE');
    $( "#esliderval" ).text(ui.value);
  }
});
drawkmeans(0, 'GLE'); // init
$( "#esliderval" ).text(0);

</script>
<br>
Each of the original stops are represented by a transparent circle of 
corresponding color (see key up top). Each optimal stop appears as a solid 
circle of the same color with a black border.

In 2014, the [MBTA proposed removing four stops from the B line](http://www.bu.edu/today/2014/t-may-eliminate-two-green-line-b-stops/): 
BU West, St
Paul St., Pleasant St., and Babcock St., replacing them with one new stop just
west of BU West and a second between Babcock St. and Pleasant St. The results
here agreed; if we were to use this experiment to improve the Green Line B
branch by just one stop, it would remove the Pleasant St. and Babcock St. stops,
replacing them with a new stop in between. So that's pretty cool.

For details and all source code, see the project [on GitHub](https://github.com/stevejarvis/course-2016-spr-proj-two/tree/master/ciestu12_sajarvis).
For similar projects, see the [Data Mechanics](http://datamechanics.io) site.
